a great lesson the archetypal tale of finding contentment in ones own backyard is portrayed in this delightful film about a wandering local government official in bhutan . while `` on the road '' the official and his co-travelers , ( monk , fair maiden , fruit seller ) reflect on the lessons of the monks stories about suffering and clinging to false concepts of stability . the pace of this film is most likely slow for american audiences but the pace is integral to highlighting the conflicts within the government officials desire to find nirvana in materialism